      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;astro-and-comets&#34;&gt;Astro and Comets&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;2024-10-21-finally-the-comet-was-seen&#34;&gt;2024-10-21: Finally the comet was seen!&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The maximum brightness was missed due to cloudy weather. At a&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magnitude_(astronomy)&#34;&gt;magnitude&lt;/a&gt; of 4.4 the observation was difficult to the naked eyes.&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adaptation_(eye)&#34;&gt;Dark-adaption&lt;/a&gt; and&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Averted_vision&#34;&gt;averted-vision&lt;/a&gt; helped a lot, and of course the optical tools:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;8x20 Trinovid binocular&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;10&amp;quot; &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dobsonian_telescope&#34;&gt;Dobsonian&lt;/a&gt;  with 2&amp;quot; wide-angle&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eyepiece#Erfle&#34;&gt;Erfle-eyepiece&lt;/a&gt;, two degree&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Field_of_view&#34;&gt;field-of-view&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digital_single-lens_reflex_camera&#34;&gt;DSLR&lt;/a&gt;  on a tripod, using a fixed focal length&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zeiss_Planar&#34;&gt;50mm-Planar&lt;/a&gt;  (f/1,7), which acts as 75mm due to CropFactor.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;c2023-a3----tsuchinshan---atlas&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C/2023_A3_(Tsuchinshan%E2%80%93ATLAS)&#34;&gt;C/2023 A3 &lt;/a&gt;    &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Purple_Mountain_Observatory&#34;&gt;Tsuchinshan&lt;/a&gt; - &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Asteroid_Terrestrial-impact_Last_Alert_System&#34;&gt;ATLAS&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ephemeris&#34;&gt;Ephemerides&lt;/a&gt;  as&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia